SAP FICO/PS Consultant
SAP FICO/PS Consultant
Location:  Singapore
SAP FICO/PS Consultant- Permanent- Singapore
Responsibilities:
• Analyse, understand and support SAP FI, CO and PS processes and business requirements.
• Configure the SAP system to facilitate FI, CO & PS business processes and transaction flows of all financial transactions for the company codes.
• Work closely with other team members to understand integration between FI, CO, PS and other Business Application areas.
• Lead and/or participate in project team for implementation of SAP company code and/or modules.
• Work closely with global and other locations on the coordination of global business process development and SAP configuration settings.
• Work with users and other team members in solving complex process and transformation issues, data cleansing and migration/conversions.
• Ensure quality of process and functional developments of SAP template are followed.
• Ensure processes and documentations for changes to Production System are followed.
• Contribute to executing, organizing and testing in cooperation with super users/process experts for new releases of SAP template and other relevant test categories.
• Support user community in daily operation. Resolve and close-out users’ enquires, service requests and incidents reported.
• Support user community in implementation of new functional releases and processes.
• Delivery of instructor led end user training and workshops, including user documentation, for super users and process experts due to process changes and/or new development of template for SAP.
• Responsible to assigned projects, adopt methodology in project management and documentation; deliver solution that conform to user requirements and on-time delivery.
• Interfaces with other IT personnel to accomplish project goals.
• Keep up-to-date with current and future technologies and system capabilities in focus area.
• Meet the expected companies HSE standard and quality of services.
Requirements:
• University degree in Information Technology/Computer Science or equivalent qualifications.
• Strong depth and breadth of expertise in FI/CO and PS
• More than 8 years of functional, configuration and user support experience with FI/CO/PS.
• Minimum 5 years of experience and strong command of business (finance and accounting) principles, processes and concepts related to manufacturing and services.
• Minimum 3 full life-cycle implementations of SAP FI/CO/PS.
• Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English. Mandarin speaking will be an added advantage.
• Possess project management skills.
• Ability to lead complex and cross-functional project teams and manages critical timelines.
• Demonstrated advanced analytical and problem-solving skills to analyse business requirements and translate them into system-supported solutions.
• Must be able to handle multiple priorities at one time and results- oriented.
• Must work well both independently and in a team environment.
• Must be a self-starter.
• Familiarity with Microsoft technologies and environments
Please can all interested candidates forward a copy of there up to date CV to michelle.hoangcv@amoriabond.com.sg
for immediate interview.
